    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There's two options here to solve this: \r\n\r\n1. We create a new widget called `<Snippet/>` that has the same interface as the `<Highlight/>` one except that it will look for `_snippetResult` instead of `_highlightResult`. \r\n\r\n2. We add an optional prop `path` to the `<Highlight/>` component that allow a user to specify it's own path to the right structure. Default would be `_highlighResult`. \r\n\r\nI tend to prefer the first one, I think it's clearer: if you want to display a snippet, you use the snippet widget. WDYT @vvo and @bobylito?",
